  carbohydrates: 84 g
  protein: 27 g
---

Boil a #large pot{} of water. Peel and finely chop @onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and finely chopped). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{2}(finely chopped). Finely chop the @sun dried tomatoes{2}(finely chopped) and the @green chilli{1}(finely chopped). Chop your @tiger prawns{120} to the size of your 'pinky' fingernail.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, cook the onion, garlic and sun-dried tomatoes. Sprinkle in the chilli together with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook for ~{5%minutes} and be careful not to let the ingredients burn.

Add in the @chopped tomatoes{1}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few grinds of @black pepper{}. Let the mixture bubble away on medium-low heat for around ~{10%minutes} until you have a nice thick sauce.

Cook your pasta in the boiling water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for around ~{11%minutes}. Once the pasta is 'al dente' drain it. > 'Al dente' means it is cooked but there is just a hint of firmness left in the middle.

Once your pasta sauce has thickened up, stir in the raw prawns and cook them for a few mins until they turn pink.

Next, drop your drained @wheat spaghetti{180} into the pan with the tomato sauce. Sprinkle over the parsley, then toss the ingredients together to mix them. If you don't fancy redecorating the kitchen, then you can always give it a good stir instead.

Serve and gobble immediately.